#!/usr/bin/env python
"""
CESMLC V9 - weak-label training dataset builder
====================================================

This version keeps the full engineered/audit data, but creates model-ready training
files that do not use RAN reference fields, RCA fields, rule columns, seed scores,
or report-only fields as model inputs.

Use either:
  1) --engineered-features existing_engineered.csv
  2) --input raw.csv to call the feature-engineering module again

Main outputs:
  - cesmlc_v9_training_dataset.csv                       full weak-labeled audit table
  - cesmlc_v9_model_ready_training_dataset.csv            all trainable rows before balancing
  - cesmlc_v9_balanced_model_ready_training_dataset.csv   recommended training input
  - cesmlc_v9_model_input_column_policy.csv               which columns are allowed/excluded for model training
"""
